[WORK DONE]: First thing was to get the video sorted so I ran it through my normal filters. I increased the lum and gamma slightly, then added a lot more contrast to equal it out.Also increase the color by increasing the chroma. After I needed to reduce the glares so I lowered the rgb black base to tone all glares down. To reduce the video noise I used a video noise reduction filter and then sharpened it up some more with a contour filter. Only left one other problem on the video, then noticed a couple of times through the film the cam drops down and it leaves a black line across the top of the screen. So I cropped to the lowest point and left it like that throughout the film  hence the different res on my release compared to the others. Original 704ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬â€288 mine 704ÃƒÆ’Ã¢â‚¬â€274. Now the hard part: syncing  :lol: Firstly I re-encoded the audio file in adobe audition, ran a hiss removal filter and then changed the EQ on it. Sounds better to me, but each to their own. After I needed to shrink the audio file in sony sound forge to match the runtime of the video and then it was a case of finding the first setting (audio correction) and syncing it from there. Needed to make several cuts where it went out of sync again but got there in the end. Oh and YES THERE IS NO SUBS FOR THIS. Before people start asking or moaning ;-)

